<font color="#FF0000">TO COOK</font><br>
<tt>Mon Dec 22 20:09:12 US/Eastern 1997
</tt><p>
Cook,<br><br>
I remember, quite well, your post about Mrs Van De Walle.<br><br>
If you browse the different Veteran's locators on the Net, you always find a few people who are looking for comrades of a lost brother, son, or husband. There is a need on the part of the surviving members of the family.<br><br>
I found a lady who is the mother of one of my friends, who was killed in RVN, this past summer - by using the resources available on the Net. I wrote her a short letter explaining who I was and how I knew her son. After writing the letter, I decided not to send it, but the next morning I mailed it anyway. <br><br>
I'm glad that I did. About 3 days later I received a call from Jerry's mom. She was most appreciative of the thoughts I expressed in my letter to her. We had a very nice chat.<br><br>
Something that I never had realized until then was that there was a strong need OF MY OWN to relate to her how I had carried and shared the burden of her loss all those years.<br><br>
In short, *I* felt a whole lot better, myself.<br><br>
Thanks Cook.<br><br>

<p><code>-- wingman@greene.xtn.net  (Tom Dier) </code><p>


